obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (8145)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 16
  title `Establishment of State Disaster Management Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8145&sectionno=14&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every State Government shall, as soon as may be after the issue of the notification under sub-section (1) of section 3, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, establish a State Disaster Management Authority for the State with such name as`
  line `may be specified in the notification of the State Government.`
  line
  line `(2) A State Authority shall consist of the Chairperson and such number of other members, not`
  line `exceeding nine, as may be prescribed by the State Government and, unless the rules otherwise provide,`
  line `the State Authority shall consist of the following members, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the Chief Minister of the State, who shall be Chairperson, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(b) other members, not exceeding eight, to be nominated by the Chairperson of the State`
  line Authority;
  line
  line `(c) the Chairperson of the State Executive Committee, ex officio.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairperson of the State Authority may designate one of the members nominated under`
  line `clause (b) of sub-section (2) to be the Vice-Chairperson of the State Authority.`
  line
  line `(4) The Chairperson of the State Executive Committee shall be the Chief Executive Officer of the`
  line `State Authority, ex officio:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of a Union territory having Legislative Assembly, except the Union territory`
  line `of Delhi, the Chief Minister shall be the Chairperson of the Authority established under this section and in`
  line `case of other Union territories, the Lieutenant Governor or the Administrator shall be the Chairperson of`
  line `that Authority:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Lieutenant Governor of the Union territory of Delhi shall be the Chairperson`
  line `and the Chief Minister thereof shall be the Vice-Chairperson of the State Authority.`
  line
  line `(5) The term of office and conditions of service of members of the State Authority shall be such as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (8146)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 17
  title `Meetings of the State Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8146&sectionno=15&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Authority shall meet as and when necessary`
  line `and at such time and place as the Chairperson of the State Authority may think fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson of the State Authority shall preside over the meetings of the State Authority.`
  line
  line `(3) If for any reason, the Chairperson of the State Authority is unable to attend the meeting of the`
  line `State Authority, the Vice-Chairperson of the State Authority shall preside at the meeting.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (8147)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 18
  title `Appointment of officers and other employees of State Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8147&sectionno=16&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The State Government`
  line `shall provide the State Authority with such officers, consultants and employees, as it considers necessary,`
  line `for carrying out the functions of the State Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (8148)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 19
  title `Constitution of advisory committee by the State Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8148&sectionno=17&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) A State Authority may, as`
  line `and when it considers necessary, constitute an advisory committee, consisting of experts in the field of`
  line `disaster management and having practical experience of disaster management to make recommendations`
  line `on different aspects of disaster management.`
  line
  line `(2) The members of the advisory committee shall be paid such allowances as may be prescribed by`
  line `the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (8149)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 20
  title `Powers and functions of State Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8149&sectionno=18&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, a State`
  line `Authority shall have the responsibility for laying down policies and plans for disaster management in the`
  line State.
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of provisions contained in sub-section (1), the State Authority`
  line may---
  line
  line `(a) lay down the State disaster management policy;`
  line
  line `^1[(b) coordinate the preparation, and approve the State Plan in accordance with the guidelines laid`
  line `down by the National Authority;]`
  line
  line `(c) approve the disaster management plans prepared by the departments of the Government of the`
  line State;
  line
  line `^2[(ca) approve the District Plan and Urban Plan, prepared by the District Authorities and Urban`
  line `Authorities respectively, in accordance with the National Plan and State Plan;]`
  line
  line `(d) lay down guidelines to be followed by the departments of the Government of the State for the`
  line `purposes of integration of measures for prevention of disasters and mitigation in their development`
  line `plans and projects and provide necessary technical assistance therefor;`
  line
  line `(e) coordinate the implementation of the State Plan;`
  line
  line `(f) recommend provision of funds for mitigation and preparedness measures;`
  line
  line `(g) review the development plans of the different departments of the State and ensure that`
  line `prevention and mitigation measures are integrated therein;`
  line
  line `(h) review the measures being taken for mitigation, capacity building and preparedness by the`
  line `departments of the Government of the State and issue such guidelines as may be necessary.`
  line
  line `^2[(i) take stock of the entire range of disaster risks in the State, periodically including emerging`
  line `disaster risks, and take necessary measures for their mitigation;`
  line
  line `(j) coordinate and monitor the implementation of the National Policy, the National Plan and the`
  line `State Plan;`
  line
  line `(k) lay down guidelines for preparation of disaster management plan by the Departments of the`
  line `Government of the State, the District Authorities and the Urban Authorities;`
  line
  line `(l) promote general education, awareness and community training in regard to the forms of`
  line `disasters to which different parts of the State are vulnerable and the measures that may be taken by`
  line `such community to prevent the disaster, mitigate and respond to such disaster;`
  line
  line `(m) provide necessary technical assistance or give advice to the District Authorities, local`
  line `authorities and Urban Authorities for carrying out their functions effectively;`
  line
  line `(n) provide information to the National Authority relating to different aspects of disaster`
  line management;
  line
  line `(o) lay down guidelines for standards of relief to persons affected by disasters in the State:`
  line `Provided that such standards shall in no case be less than the minimum standards in the guidelines`
  line `laid down by the National Authority in this regard;`
  line
  line `(p) maintain the State disaster database and provide inputs to the National disaster database.]`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairperson of the State Authority shall, in the case of emergency, have power to exercise all`
  line `or any of the powers of the State Authority but the exercise of such powers shall be subject to ex post`
  line `facto ratification of the State Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2025, s. 10, for clause (b) (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (8150)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 21
  title Omitted.
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
