obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (8151)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 22
  title `Constitution of State Executive Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2025, s. 12 (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8151&sectionno=20&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government shall, immediately`
  line `after issue of notification under sub-section (1) of section 14, constitute a State Executive Committee to`
  line `assist the State Authority in the performance of its functions and to coordinate action in accordance with`
  line `the guidelines laid down by the State Authority and ensure the compliance of directions issued by the`
  line `State Government under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Executive Committee shall consist of the following members, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the Chief Secretary to the State Government, who shall be Chairperson, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(b) four Secretaries to the Government of the State of such departments as the State Government`
  line `may think fit, ex officio.`
  line
  line `^1[(c) the Director General of Police of the State shall be member of the State Executive`
  line `Committee, ex officio.]`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairperson of the State Executive Committee shall exercise such powers and perform such`
  line `functions as may be prescribed by the State Government and such other powers and functions as may be`
  line `delegated to him by the State Authority.`
  line
  line `(4) The procedure to be followed by the State Executive Committee in exercise of its powers and`
  line `discharge of its functions shall be such as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (8152)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 23
  title `Constitution of sub-committees by State Executive Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8152&sectionno=21&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Executive`
  line `Committee may, as and when it considers necessary, constitute one or more sub-committees, for efficient`
  line `discharge of its functions.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Executive Committee shall, from amongst its members, appoint the Chairperson of the`
  line `sub-committee referred to in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `3) Any person associated as an expert with any sub-committee may be paid such allowances as may`
  line `be prescribed by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (8153)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 24
  title `Functions of the State Executive Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8153&sectionno=22&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Executive Committee shall have`
  line `the responsibility for implementing the National Plan and State Plan and act as the coordinating and`
  line `monitoring body for management of disaster in the State.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of sub-section (1), the State Executive`
  line `Committee may---`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
  line
  line `(b) examine the vulnerability of different parts of the State to different forms of disasters and`
  line `specify measures to be taken for their prevention or mitigation;`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
  line
  line `(d) monitor the implementation of disaster management plans prepared by the departments of the`
  line `Government of the State ^2[, the District Authorities and the Urban Authorities;`
  line
  line `(e) monitor the implementation of the guidelines laid down by the State Authority for integrating`
  line `of measures for prevention of disasters and mitigation by the departments in their development plans`
  line `and projects;`
  line
  line `(f) evaluate preparedness at all governmental or non-governmental levels to respond to any`
  line `threatening disaster situation or disaster and give directions, where necessary, for enhancing such`
  line preparedness;
  line
  line `(g) coordinate response in the event of any threatening disaster situation or disaster;`
  line
  line `(h) give directions to any Department of the Government of the State or any other authority or`
  line `body in the State regarding actions to be taken in response to any threatening disaster situation or`
  line disaster;
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `(j) advise, assist and coordinate the activities of the Departments of the Government of the State,`
  line `District Authorities ^4[, Urban Authorities,] statutory bodies and other governmental and nongovernmental organisations engaged in disaster management;`
  line
  line `^5* * * * *`
  line
  line `(l) advise the State Government regarding all financial matters in relation to disaster`
  line management;
  line
  line `(m) examine the construction, in any local area in the State and, if it is of the opinion that the`
  line `standards laid for such construction for the prevention of disaster is not being or has not been`
  line `followed, may direct the ^6[District Authority, Urban Authority or the local authority], as the case may`
  line `be, to take such action as may be necessary to secure compliance of such standards;`
  line
  line `^7* * * * *`
  line
  line `(o) lay down, review and update State level response plans and guidelines and ensure that the`
  line `district level plans are prepared, reviewed and updated;`
  line
  line `(p) ensure that communication systems are in order and the disaster management drills are carried`
  line `out periodically;`
  line
  line `(q) perform such other functions as may be assigned to it by the State Authority or as it may`
  line `consider necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Cls. (a) and (c) omitted by Act 10 of 2025, s. 13, (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 13, ibid., for "and District Authorities" (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  line
  line `3. Cl. (i) omitted by s. 13,ibid. (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by , s. 13, ibid. (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  line
  line `5. Cl. (k) omitted by s. 13, ibid. (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 13,ibid., for "District Authority or the local authority" (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  line
  line `7. Cl. (n) omitted by s. 13,ibid. (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (8154)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 25
  title `State Plan.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8154&sectionno=23&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be a plan for disaster management for every State to be called the`
  line `State Disaster Management Plan.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) The State Authority shall coordinate the preparation of the State Plan having regard to the`
  line `National Plan and guidelines laid down by the National Authority, and in consultation with local`
  line `authorities, District Authorities, Urban Authorities and the peoples representatives as the State Authority`
  line `may deem fit.]`
  line
  line `^2[(3) The State Plan shall be approved by the State Authority.]`
  line
  line `(4) The State Plan shall include,---`
  line
  line `^3[(a) the exposure of different parts of the State to different hazards and vulnerability of its`
  line `people, assets, infrastructure, livelihood and economic activity to those hazards;]`
  line
  line `(b) the measures to be adopted for prevention and mitigation of disasters;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner in which the mitigation measures shall be integrated with the development plans`
  line `and projects;`
  line
  line `(d) the capacity-building and preparedness measures to be taken;`
  line
  line `(e) the roles and responsibilities of each Department of the Government of the State in relation to`
  line `the measures specified in clauses (b), (c) and (d) above;`
  line
  line `(f) the roles and responsibilities of different Departments of the Government of the State in`
  line `responding to any threatening disaster situation or disaster.`
  line
  line `^4[(5) The State Authority shall review the State Plan once in every three years and update atleast once`
  line `in every five years.]`
  line
  line `(6) Appropriate provisions shall be made by the State Government for financing for the measures to`
  line `be carried out under the State Plan.`
  line
  line `(7) Copies of the State Plan referred to in sub-sections (2) and (5) shall be made available to the`
  line `Departments of the Government of the State and such Departments shall draw up their own plans in`
  line `accordance with the State Plan.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2025, s. 14, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 14, ibid., for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 14, ibid., for clause (a) (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 14, ibid., for sub-section (5) (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (8155)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 26
  title `Powers and functions of State Executive Committee in the event of threatening disaster situation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2025, s. 15 (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8155&sectionno=24&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of, assisting and protecting the community affected by disaster or providing`
  line `relief to such community or, preventing or combating disruption or dealing with the effects of any`
  line `threatening disaster situation, the State Executive Committee may`
  line
  line `(a) control and restrict, vehicular traffic to, from or within, the vulnerable or affected area;`
  line
  line `(b) control and restrict the entry of any person into, his movement within and departure from, a`
  line `vulnerable or affected area;`
  line
  line `(c) remove debris, conduct search and carry out rescue operations;`
  line
  line `(d) provide shelter, food, drinking water, essential provisions, healthcare and services in`
  line `accordance with the standards laid down by the National Authority and State Authority;`
  line
  line `(e) give direction to the concerned Department of the Government of the State, any District`
  line `Authority ^1[, any Urban Authority] or other authority, within the local limits of the State to take such measure or steps for`
  line `rescue, evacuation or providing immediate relief saving lives or property, as may be necessary in its`
  line opinion;
  line
  line `(f) require any department of the Government of the State or any other body or authority or`
  line `person in charge of any relevant resources to make available the resources for the purposes of`
  line `emergency response, rescue and relief;`
  line
  line `(g) require experts and consultants in the field of disasters to provide advice and assistance for`
  line `rescue and relief;`
  line
  line `(h) procure exclusive or preferential use of amenities from any authority or person as and when`
  line required;
  line
  line `(i) construct temporary bridges or other necessary structures and demolish unsafe structures`
  line `which may be hazardous to public;`
  line
  line `(j) ensure that non-governmental organisations carry out their activities in an equitable and nondiscriminatory`
  line manner;
  line
  line `(k) disseminate information to public to deal with any threatening disaster situation or disaster;`
  line
  line `(l) take such steps as the Central Government or the State Government may direct in this regard`
  line `or take such other steps as are required or warranted by the form of any threatening disaster situation`
  line `or disaster.`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (8156)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 27
  title `Constitution of District Disaster Management Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2025, s. 16, for clause (f) (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8156&sectionno=25&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every State Government shall,`
  line `as soon as may be after issue of notification under sub-section (1) of section 14, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, establish a District Disaster Management Authority for every district in the State with`
  line `such name as may be specified in that notification.`
  line
  line `(2) The District Authority shall consist of the Chairperson and such number of other members, not`
  line `exceeding seven, as may be prescribed by the State Government, and unless the rules otherwise provide,`
  line `it shall consist of the following, namely:`
  line
  line `(a) the Collector or District Magistrate or Deputy Commissioner, as the case may be, of the`
  line `district who shall be Chairperson, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(b) the elected representative of the local authority who shall be the co-Chairperson, ex officio:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the Tribal Areas, as referred to in the Sixth Schedule to the Constitution, the`
  line `Chief Executive Member of the district council of autonomous district, shall be the co-Chairperson,`
  line `ex officio;`
  line
  line `(c) the Chief Executive Officer of the District Authority, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(d) the Superintendent of Police, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(e) the Chief Medical Officer of the district, ex officio;`
  line
  line `^1[(f) not exceeding two other Members to be appointed by the State Government who may be`
  line `taken from other district level officers, disaster management experts and civil society organisation.]`
  line
  line `(3) In any district where zila parishad exists, the Chairperson thereof shall be the co-Chairperson of`
  line `the District Authority.`
  line
  line `(4) The State Government shall appoint an officer not below the rank of Additional Collector or`
  line `Additional District Magistrate or Additional Deputy Commissioner, as the case may be, of the district to`
  line `be the Chief Executive Officer of the District Authority to exercise such powers and perform such`
  line `functions as may be prescribed by the State Government and such other powers and functions as may be`
  line `delegated to him by the District Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (8157)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 28
  title `Powers of Chairperson of District Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8157&sectionno=26&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson of the District Authority`
  line `shall, in addition to presiding over the meetings of the District Authority, exercise and discharge such`
  line `powers and functions of the District Authority as the District Authority may delegate to him.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson of the District Authority shall, in the case of an emergency, have power to`
  line `exercise all or any of the powers of the District Authority but the exercise of such powers shall be subject`
  line `to ex post facto ratification of the District Authority.`
  line
  line `(3) The District Authority or the Chairperson of the District Authority may, by general or special`
  line `order, in writing, delegate such of its or his powers and functions, under sub-section (1) or (2), as the case`
  line `may be, to the Chief Executive Officer of the District Authority, subject to such conditions and`
  line `limitations, if any, as it or he deems fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (8158)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 29
  title Meetings.
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8158&sectionno=27&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `The District Authority shall meet as and when necessary and at such time and place`
  line `as the Chairperson may think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (8159)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 30
  title `Constitution of advisory committees and other committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8159&sectionno=28&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) The District Authority may,`
  line `as and when it considers necessary, constitute one or more advisory committees and other committees for`
  line `the efficient discharge of its functions.`
  line
  line `(2) The District Authority shall, from amongst its members, appoint the Chairperson of the`
  line `Committee referred to in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) Any person associated as an expert with any committee or sub-committee constituted under`
  line `sub-section (1) may be paid such allowances as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (8160)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 31
  title `Appointment of officers and other employees of District Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8160&sectionno=29&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `The State Government`
  line `shall provide the District Authority with such officers, consultants and other employees as it considers`
  line `necessary for carrying out the functions of District Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (8161)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 32
  title `Powers and functions of District Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8161&sectionno=30&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) The District Authority shall act as the district`
  line `planning, coordinating and implementing body for disaster management and take all measures for the`
  line `purposes of disaster management in the district in accordance with the guidelines laid down by the`
  line `National Authority and the State Authority.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of sub-section (1), the District Authority`
  line may—
  line
  line `(i) prepare a disaster management plan including district response plan for the district;`
  line
  line `(ii) coordinate and monitor the implementation of the National Policy, State Policy, National`
  line `Plan, State Plan and District Plan;`
  line
  line `(iii) ensure that the areas in the district vulnerable to disasters are identified and measures for the`
  line `prevention of disasters and the mitigation of its effects are undertaken by the departments of the`
  line `Government at the district level as well as by the local authorities;`
  line
  line `(iv) ensure that the guidelines for prevention of disasters, mitigation of its effects, preparedness`
  line `and response measures as laid down by the National Authority and the State Authority are followed`
  line `by all departments of the Government at the district level and the local authorities in the district;`
  line
  line `(v) give directions to different authorities at the district level and local authorities to take such`
  line `other measures for the prevention or mitigation of disasters as may be necessary;`
  line
  line `(vi) lay down guidelines for prevention of disaster management plans by the department of the`
  line `Government at the districts level and local authorities in the district;`
  line
  line `(vii) monitor the implementation of disaster management plans prepared by the Departments of`
  line `the Government at the district level;`
  line
  line `(viii) lay down guidelines to be followed by the Departments of the Government at the district`
  line `level for purposes of integration of measures for prevention of disasters and mitigation in their`
  line `development plans and projects and provide necessary technical assistance therefor;`
  line
  line `(ix) monitor the implementation of measures referred to in clause (viii);`
  line
  line `(x) review the state of capabilities for responding to any disaster or threatening disaster situation`
  line `in the district and give directions to the relevant departments or authorities at the district level for`
  line `their up gradation as may be necessary;`
  line
  line `(xi) review the preparedness measures and give directions to the concerned departments at the`
  line `district level or other concerned authorities where necessary for bringing the preparedness measures`
  line `to the levels required for responding effectively to any disaster or threatening disaster situation;`
  line
  line `(xii) organise and coordinate specialised training programmes for different levels of officers,`
  line `employees and voluntary rescue workers in the district;`
  line
  line `(xiii) facilitate community training and awareness programmes for prevention of disaster or`
  line `mitigation with the support of local authorities, governmental and non-governmental organisations;`
  line
  line `(xiv) set up, maintain, review and upgrade the mechanism for early warnings and dissemination of`
  line `proper information to public;`
  line
  line `(xv) prepare, review and update district level response plan and guidelines;`
  line
  line `(xvi) coordinate response to any threatening disaster situation or disaster;`
  line
  line `(xvii) ensure that the Departments of the Government at the district level and the local authorities`
  line `prepare their response plans in accordance with the district response plan;`
  line
  line `(xviii) lay down guidelines for, or give direction to, the concerned Department of the Government`
  line `at the district level or any other authorities within the local limits of the district to take measures to`
  line `respond effectively to any threatening disaster situation or disaster;`
  line
  line `(xix) advise, assist and coordinate the activities of the Departments of the Government at the`
  line `district level, statutory bodies and other governmental and non-governmental organisations in the`
  line `district engaged in the disaster management;`
  line
  line `(xx) coordinate with, and give guidelines to, local authorities in the district to ensure that`
  line `measures for the prevention or mitigation of threatening disaster situation or disaster in the district are`
  line `carried out promptly and effectively;`
  line
  line `(xxi) provide necessary technical assistance or give advise to the local authorities in the district`
  line `for carrying out their functions;`
  line
  line `(xxii) review development plans prepared by the Departments of the Government at the district`
  line `level, statutory authorities or local authorities with a view to make necessary provisions therein for`
  line `prevention of disaster or mitigation;`
  line
  line `(xxiii) examine the construction in any area in the district and, if it is of the opinion that the`
  line `standards for the prevention of disaster or mitigation laid down for such construction is not being or`
  line `has not been followed, may direct the concerned authority to take such action as may be necessary to`
  line `secure compliance of such standards;`
  line
  line `(xxiv) identify buildings and places which could, in the event of any threatening disaster situation`
  line `or disaster, be used as relief centers or camps and make arrangements for water supply and sanitation`
  line `in such buildings or places;`
  line
  line `(xxv) establish stockpiles of relief and rescue materials or ensure preparedness to make such`
  line `materials available at a short notice;`
  line
  line `(xxvi) provide information to the State Authority relating to different aspects of disaster`
  line management;
  line
  line `(xxvii) encourage the involvement of non-governmental organisations and voluntary socialwelfare`
  line `institutions working at the grassroots level in the district for disaster management;`
  line
  line `(xxviii) ensure communication systems are in order, and disaster management drills are carried`
  line `out periodically;`
  line
  line `(xxix) perform such other functions as the State Government or State Authority may assign to it or`
  line `as it deems necessary for disaster management in the District.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (8162)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 33
  title `District Plan.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2025, s. 17, for "annually" (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8162&sectionno=31&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be a plan for disaster management for every district of the State.`
  line
  line `(2) The District Plan shall be prepared by the District Authority, after consultation with the local`
  line `authorities and having regard to the National Plan and the State Plan, to be approved by the State`
  line Authority.
  line
  line `(3) The District Plan shall include`
  line
  line `(a) the areas in the district vulnerable to different forms of disasters;`
  line
  line `(b) the measures to be taken, for prevention and mitigation of disaster, by the Departments of the`
  line `Government at the district level and local authorities in the district;`
  line
  line `(c) the capacity-building and preparedness measures required to be taken by the Departments of`
  line `the Government at the district level and the local authorities in the district to respond to any`
  line `threatening disaster situation or disaster;`
  line
  line `(d) the response plans and procedures, in the event of a disaster, providing for`
  line
  line `(i) allocation of responsibilities to the Departments of the Government at the district level and`
  line `the local authorities in the district;`
  line
  line `(ii) prompt response to disaster and relief thereof;`
  line
  line `(iii) procurement of essential resources;`
  line
  line `(iv) establishment of communication links; and`
  line
  line `(v) the dissemination of information to the public;`
  line
  line `(e) such other matters as may be required by the State Authority.`
  line
  line `(4) The District Plan shall be reviewed and updated ^1[at least once in every two years or earlier as`
  line necessary].
  line
  line `(5) The copies of the District Plan referred to in sub-sections (2) and (4) shall be made available to the`
  line `Departments of the Government in the district.`
  line
  line `(6) The District Authority shall send a copy of the District Plan to the State Authority which shall`
  line `forward it to the State Government.`
  line
  line `(7) The District Authority shall, review from time to time, the implementation of the Plan and issue`
  line `such instructions to different departments of the Government in the district as it may deem necessary for`
  line `the implementation thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (8163)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 34
  title `Plans by different authorities at district level and their implementation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8163&sectionno=32&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Every office of the`
  line `Government of India and of the State Government at the district level and the local authorities shall,`
  line `subject to the supervision of the District Authority,—`
  line
  line `(a) prepare a disaster management plan setting out the following, namely:—`
  line
  line `(i) provisions for prevention and mitigation measures as provided for in the District Plan and`
  line `as is assigned to the department or agency concerned;`
  line
  line `(ii) provisions for taking measures relating to capacity-building and preparedness as laid`
  line `down in the District Plan;`
  line
  line `(iii) the response plans and procedures, in the event of, any threatening disaster situation or`
  line disaster;
  line
  line `(b) coordinate the preparation and the implementation of its plan with those of the other`
  line `organisations at the district level including local authority, communities and other stakeholders;`
  line
  line `(c) regularly review and update the plan; and`
  line
  line `(d) submit a copy of its disaster management plan, and of any amendment thereto, to the District`
  line Authority.
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (8164)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 35
  title `Requisition by the District Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8164&sectionno=33&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `The District Authority may by order require any officer`
  line `or any Department at the district level or any local authority to take such measures for the prevention or`
  line `mitigation of disaster, or to effectively respond to it, as may be necessary, and such officer or department`
  line `shall be bound to carry out such order.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (8165)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 36
  title `Powers and functions of District Authority in the event of any threatening disaster situation or disaster.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8165&sectionno=34&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of assisting, protecting or providing relief to the community, in response to`
  line `any threatening disaster situation or disaster, the District Authority may—`
  line
  line `(a) give directions for the release and use of resources available with any Department of the`
  line `Government and the local authority in the district;`
  line
  line `(b) control and restrict vehicular traffic to, from and within, the vulnerable or affected area;`
  line
  line `(c) control and restrict the entry of any person into, his movement within and departure from, a`
  line `vulnerable or affected area;`
  line
  line `(d) remove debris, conduct search and carry out rescue operations;`
  line
  line `(e) provide shelter, food, drinking water and essential provisions, healthcare and services;`
  line
  line `(f) establish emergency communication systems in the affected area;`
  line
  line `(g) make arrangements for the disposal of the unclaimed dead bodies;`
  line
  line `(h) recommend to any Department of the Government of the State or any authority or body under`
  line `that Government at the district level to take such measures as are necessary in its opinion;`
  line
  line `(i) require experts and consultants in the relevant fields to advise and assist as it may deem`
  line necessary;
  line
  line `(j) procure exclusive or preferential use of amenities from any authority or person;`
  line
  line `(k) construct temporary bridges or other necessary structures and demolish structures which may`
  line `be hazardous to public or aggravate the effects of the disaster;`
  line
  line `(l) ensure that the non-governmental organisations carry out their activities in an equitable and`
  line `non-discriminatory manner;`
  line
  line `(m) take such other steps as may be required or warranted to be taken in such a situation.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (8166)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 37
  title `Central Government to take measures.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8166&sectionno=35&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Central`
  line `Government shall take all such measures as it deems necessary or expedient for the purpose of disaster`
  line management.
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of sub-section (1), the`
  line `measures which the Central Government may take under that sub-section include measures with respect`
  line `to all or any of the following matters, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) ^1[coordinate and monitor actions] of the Ministries or Departments of the Government of`
  line `India, State Governments, National Authority, State Authorities, governmental and non-governmental`
  line `organisations in relation to disaster management;`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `(c) ensure appropriate allocation of funds for prevention of disaster, mitigation, capacity-building`
  line `and preparedness by the Ministries or Departments of the Government of India;`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `(e) cooperation and assistance to State Governments, as requested by them or otherwise deemed`
  line `appropriate by it;`
  line
  line `(f) deployment of naval, military and air forces, other armed forces of the Union or any other`
  line `civilian personnel as may be required for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) coordination with the United Nations agencies, international organisations and governments`
  line `of foreign countries for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(h) establish institutions for research, training, and developmental programmes in the field of`
  line `disaster management;`
  line
  line `^3[(ha) notify the Ministries or Departments of the Government of India which shall have the`
  line `responsibility for monitoring, early warning, prevention, mitigation, preparedness and capacity`
  line `building with regard to disasters arising from various hazards;]`
  line
  line `(i) such other matters as it deems necessary or expedient for the purpose of securing effective`
  line `implementation of the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may extend such support to other countries affected by major disaster as`
  line `it may deem appropriate.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2025, s. 18, for "coordination of actions" (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  line
  line `2. Cls. (b) and (d) omitted by s. 18,ibid. (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 18, ibid. (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (8167)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 38
  title `Responsibilities of Ministries or Departments of Government of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8167&sectionno=36&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the`
  line `responsibility of every Ministry or Department of the Government of India to---`
  line
  line `(a) take measures necessary for prevention of disasters, mitigation, preparedness and capacitybuilding`
  line `in accordance with the guidelines laid down by the National Authority;`
  line
  line `(b) integrate into its development plans and projects, the measures for prevention or mitigation of`
  line `disasters in accordance with the guidelines laid down by the National Authority;`
  line
  line `(c) respond effectively and promptly to any threatening disaster situation or disaster in`
  line `accordance with the guidelines of the National Authority or the directions of the National Executive`
  line `Committee in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(d) review the enactments administered by it, its policies, rules and regulations, with a view to`
  line `incorporate therein the provisions necessary for prevention of disasters, mitigation or preparedness;`
  line
  line `(e) allocate funds for measures for prevention of disaster, mitigation, capacity-building and`
  line preparedness;
  line
  line `^1[(f) provide assistance to the National Authority and State Government for drawing up`
  line `mitigation, preparedness and response plans, capacity building, data collection and identification and`
  line `training of personnel in relation to disaster management;]`
  line
  line `(g) make available its resources to the National Executive Committee or a State Executive`
  line `Committee for the purposes of responding promptly and effectively to any threatening disaster`
  line `situation or disaster, including measures for---`
  line
  line `(i) providing emergency communication in a vulnerable or affected area;`
  line
  line `(ii) transporting personnel and relief goods to and from the affected area;`
  line
  line `(iii) providing evacuation, rescue, temporary shelter or other immediate relief;`
  line
  line `(iv) setting up temporary bridges, jetties and landing places;`
  line
  line `(v) providing, drinking water, essential provisions, healthcare, and services in an affected`
  line area;
  line
  line `^2[(vi) carrying out rescue and relief operations in the affected area;`
  line
  line `(vii) assessing the damage from any disaster; and`
  line
  line `(viii) carrying out the rehabilitation and re-construction;]`
  line
  line `(h) take such other actions as it may consider necessary for disaster management.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2025, s. 19, for clause (f) (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 19,ibid. (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (8168)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 39
  title `Disaster management plans of Ministries or Departments of Government of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8168&sectionno=37&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Every Ministry or Department of the Government of India shall—`
  line
  line `(a) prepare a disaster management plan specifying the following particulars, namely:—`
  line
  line `(i) the measures to be taken by it for prevention and mitigation of disasters in accordance`
  line `with the National Plan;`
  line
  line `(ii) the specifications regarding integration of mitigation measures in its development plans in`
  line `accordance with the guidelines of the National Authority and the National Executive Committee;`
  line
  line `(iii) its roles and responsibilities in relation to preparedness and capacity-building to deal with`
  line `any threatening disaster situation or disaster;`
  line
  line `(iv) its roles and responsibilities in regard to promptly and effectively responding to any`
  line `threatening disaster situation or disaster;`
  line
  line `(v) the present status of its preparedness to perform the roles and responsibilities specified in`
  line `sub-clauses (iii) and (iv);`
  line
  line `(vi) the measures required to be taken in order to enable it to perform its responsibilities`
  line `specified in sub-clauses (iii) and (iv);`
  line
  line `(b) review and update annually the plan referred to in clause (a);`
  line
  line `(c) forward a copy of the plan referred to in clause (a) or clause (b), as the case may be, to the`
  line `Central Government which Government shall forward a copy thereof to the National Authority for its`
  line approval.
  line
  line `(2) Every Ministry or Department of the Government of India shall—`
  line
  line `(a) make, while preparing disaster management plan under clause (a) of sub-section (1),`
  line `provisions for financing the activities specified therein;`
  line
  line `(b) furnish a status report regarding the implementation of the plan referred to in clause (a) of`
  line `sub-section (1) to the National Authority, as and when required by it.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (8169)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 40
  title `State Government to take measures.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8169&sectionno=38&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, each State`
  line `Government shall take all measures specified in the guidelines laid down by the National Authority and`
  line `such further measures as it deems necessary or expedient, for the purpose of disaster management.`
  line
  line `(2) The measures which the State Government may take under sub-section (1) include measures with`
  line `respect to all or any of the following matters, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) coordination of actions of different departments of the Government of the State, the State`
  line `Authority, District Authorities ^1[, Urban Authorities] ^2[local authorities] and other non-governmental`
  line organisations;
  line
  line `(b) cooperation and assistance in the disaster management to the National Authority and National`
  line `Executive Committee, the State Authority and the State Executive Committee, ^3[the District`
  line `Authorities and the Urban Authorities];`
  line
  line `(c) cooperation with, and assistance to, the Ministries or Departments of the Government of India`
  line `in disaster management, as requested by them or otherwise deemed appropriate by it;`
  line
  line `(d) allocation of funds for measures for prevention of disaster, mitigation, capacity-building and`
  line `preparedness by the departments of the Government of the State in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `the State Plan ^4[, the District Plans and the Urban Plans];`
  line
  line `(e) ensure that the integration of measures for prevention of disaster or mitigation by the`
  line `departments of the Government of the State in their development plans and projects;`
  line
  line `(f) integrate in the State development plan, measures to reduce or mitigate the vulnerability of`
  line `different parts of the State to different disasters;`
  line
  line `(g) ensure the preparation of disaster management plans by different departments of the State in`
  line `accordance with the guidelines laid down by the National Authority and the State Authority;`
  line
  line `(h) establishment of adequate warning systems up to the level of vulnerable communities;`
  line
  line `(i) ensure that different departments of the Government of the State ^5[, the District Authorities`
  line `and the Urban Authorities] take appropriate preparedness measures;`
  line
  line `^6[(ia) notify State-specific hazard-wise nodal Departments, which shall have the responsibility for`
  line `monitoring, early warning, prevention, mitigation, preparedness and capacity building with regard to`
  line `disasters arising from those State-specific hazards;]`
  line
  line `(j) ensure that in a threatening disaster situation or disaster, the resources of different departments`
  line `of the Government of the State are made available to the National Executive Committee or the State`
  line `Executive Committee ^7[, the District Authorities or the Urban Authorities], as the case may be, for the`
  line `purposes of effective response, rescue and relief in any threatening disaster situation or disaster;`
  line
  line `^8[(k) provide recovery and reconstruction assistance to the victims of any disaster; and]`
  line
  line `(l) such other matters as it deems necessary or expedient for the purpose of securing effective`
  line `implementation of provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2025, s. 20 (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 20, ibid., for "local authority" (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 20, ibid., for "and the District Authorities" (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 20, ibid., for "and the District Plans" (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 20, ibid., for "and the District Authorities" (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by s. 20, ibid. (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by s. 20, ibid., for "or the District Authorities" (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by s. 20, ibid., for clause (k) (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (8170)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 41
  title `Responsibilities of departments of the State Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8170&sectionno=39&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the responsibility of`
  line `every department of the Government of a State to---`
  line
  line `(a) take measures necessary for prevention of disasters, mitigation, preparedness and capacitybuilding`
  line `in accordance with the guidelines laid down by the National Authority and the State`
  line Authority;
  line
  line `(b) integrate into its development plans and projects, the measures for prevention of disaster and`
  line mitigation;
  line
  line `(c) allocate funds for prevention of disaster, mitigation, capacity-building and preparedness;`
  line
  line `(d) respond effectively and promptly to any threatening disaster situation or disaster in`
  line `accordance with the State Plan, and in accordance with the guidelines or directions of the National`
  line `Executive Committee and the State Executive Committee;`
  line
  line `(e) review the enactments administered by it, its policies, rules and regulations with a view to`
  line `incorporate therein the provisions necessary for prevention of disasters, mitigation or preparedness;`
  line
  line `(f) provide assistance, as required, by the National Executive Committee, the State Executive`
  line `Committee ^1[District Authorities and Urban Authorities], for---`
  line
  line `(i) drawing up mitigation, preparedness and response plans, capacity-building, data collection`
  line `and identification and training of personnel in relation to disaster management;`
  line
  line `(ii) assessing the damage from any disaster;`
  line
  line `(iii) carrying out rehabilitation and reconstruction;`
  line
  line `(g) make provision for resources in consultation with the State Authority for the implementation`
  line `of the District Plan by its authorities at the district level ^2[and the Urban Plan by the Urban`
  line Authorities];
  line
  line `(h) make available its resources to the National Executive Committee or the State Executive`
  line `Committee or the District Authorities ^2[or the Urban Authorities] for the purposes of responding promptly and effectively to any`
  line `disaster in the State, including measures for---`
  line
  line `(i) providing emergency communication with a vulnerable or affected area;`
  line
  line `(ii) transporting personnel and relief goods to and from the affected area;`
  line
  line `(iii) providing evacuation, rescue, temporary shelter or other immediate relief;`
  line
  line `(iv) carrying out evacuation of persons or live-stock from an area of any threatening disaster`
  line `situation or disaster;`
  line
  line `(v) setting up temporary bridges, jetties and landing places;`
  line
  line `(vi) providing drinking water, essential provisions, healthcare and services in an affected area;`
  line
  line `(i) such other actions as may be necessary for disaster management.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2025, s. 21, for "and District Authorities" (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 21, ibid. (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (8171)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 42
  title `Disaster management plan of departments of State.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8171&sectionno=40&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every department of the State`
  line `Government, in conformity with the guidelines laid down by the State Authority, shall—`
  line
  line `(a) prepare a disaster management plan which shall lay down the following :—`
  line
  line `(i) the types of disasters to which different parts of the State are vulnerable;`
  line
  line `(ii) integration of strategies for the prevention of disaster or the mitigation of its effects or`
  line `both with the development plans and programmes by the department;`
  line
  line `(iii) the roles and responsibilities of the department of the State in the event of any`
  line `threatening disaster situation or disaster and emergency support function it is required to perform;`
  line
  line `(iv) present status of its preparedness to perform such roles or responsibilities or emergency`
  line `support function under sub-clause (iii);`
  line
  line `(v) the capacity-building and preparedness measures proposed to be put into effect in order to`
  line `enable the Ministries or Departments of the Government of India to discharge their`
  line `responsibilities under section 37;`
  line
  line `(b) annually review and update the plan referred to in clause (a); and`
  line
  line `(c) furnish a copy of the plan referred to in clause (a) or clause (b), as the case may be, to the`
  line `State Authority.`
  line
  line `(2) Every department of the State Government, while preparing the plan under sub-section (1), shall`
  line `make provisions for financing the activities specified therein.`
  line
  line `(3) Every department of the State Government shall furnish an implementation status report to the`
  line `State Executive Committee regarding the implementation of the disaster management plan referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (8172)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 43
  title `Functions of the local authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2025, s. 22 (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8172&sectionno=41&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the directions of the District Authority, a local`
  line `authority shall`
  line
  line `(a) ensure that its officers and employees are trained for disaster management;`
  line
  line `(b) ensure that resources relating to disaster management are so maintained as to be readily`
  line `available for use in the event of any threatening disaster situation or disaster;`
  line
  line `(c) ensure all construction projects under it or within its jurisdiction conform to the standards and`
  line `specifications laid down for prevention of disasters and mitigation by the National Authority, State`
  line `Authority and the District Authority;`
  line
  line `(d) carry out relief, rehabilitation and reconstruction activities in the affected area in accordance`
  line `with the State Plan and the District Plan.`
  line
  line `^1[(e) prepare a disaster management plan as referred to in section 32.]`
  line
  line `(2) The local authority may take such other measures as may be necessary for the disaster`
  line management.
obj_root_law_sections_41_a:
  sectionId (96436)
  sectionNo 41A
  orderNo 44
  title `Urban Disaster Management Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2025, s. 23 (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=96436&sectionno=41A&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_41_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[41A. Urban Disaster Management Authority.--- (1) The State Government may, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, constitute a separate Urban Disaster Management Authority for their State capitals`
  line `and all cities having a Municipal Corporation, except for the National Capital Territory of Delhi and`
  line `Union territory of Chandigarh.`
  line
  line `(2) The Urban Authority constituted under sub-section (1) shall consist of the following, namely:---`
  line
  line `(i) the Municipal Commissioner--- Chairperson, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(ii) the District Collector of the District concerned---Vice Chairperson, ex officio; and`
  line
  line `(iii) such other members, with such pay and allowances as may be determined by the State`
  line `Government--- members.`
  line
  line `(3) The Urban Authority may have a separate Secretariat at such place in the district as may be`
  line `determined by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(4) The Urban Authority shall be responsible for preparation of Urban Plan, which shall be approved`
  line `by the State Authority.`
  line
  line `(5) The Urban Authority shall be responsible for coordinating the implementation of the Urban Plan.`
  line
  line `(6) The other functions and powers and such other matters relating to the Urban Authority shall be`
  line `such as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of this section, the expression "Municipal Corporation" means a`
  line `Municipal Corporation as referred to in clause (c) of article 243Q of the Constitution.]`
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (8173)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 45
  title `National Institute of Disaster Management.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8173&sectionno=42&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette appoint in this behalf, there shall be constituted`
  line `an institute to be called the National Institute of Disaster Management.`
  line
  line `(2) The National Institute of Disaster Management shall consist of such number of members as may`
  line `be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The term of office of, and vacancies among, members of the National Institute of Disaster`
  line `Management and manner of filling such vacancies shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) There shall be a governing body of the National Institute of Disaster Management which shall be`
  line `constituted by the Central Government from amongst the members of the National Institute of Disaster`
  line `Management in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) The governing body of the National Institute of Disaster Management shall exercise such powers`
  line `and discharge such functions as may be prescribed by regulations.`
  line
  line `(6) The procedure to be followed in exercise of its powers and discharge of its functions by the`
  line `governing body, and the term of office of, and the manner of filling vacancies among the members of the`
  line `governing body, shall be such as may be prescribed by regulations.`
  line
  line `(7) Until the regulations are made under this section, the Central Government may make such`
  line `regulations; and any regulation so made may be altered or rescinded by the National Institute of Disaster`
  line `Management in exercise of its powers.`
  line
  line `(8) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the National Institute of Disaster Management shall function`
  line `within the broad policies and guidelines laid down by the National Authority and be responsible for`
  line `planning and promoting training and research in the area of disaster management, documentation and`
  line `development of national level information base relating to disaster management policies, prevention`
  line `mechanisms and mitigation measures.`
  line
  line `(9) Without prejudice to the generality of the provisions contained in sub-section (8), the National`
  line `Institute, for the discharge of its functions, may—`
  line
  line `(a) develop training modules, undertake research and documentation in disaster management and`
  line `organise training programmes;`
  line
  line `(b) formulate and implement a comprehensive human resource development plan covering all`
  line `aspects of disaster management;`
  line
  line `(c) provide assistance in national level policy formulation;`
  line
  line `(d) provide required assistance to the training and research institutes for development of training`
  line `and research programmes for stakeholders including Government functionaries and undertake`
  line `training of faculty members of the State level training institutes;`
  line
  line `(e) provide assistance to the State Governments and State training institutes in the formulation of`
  line `State level policies, strategies, disaster management framework and any other assistance as may be`
  line `required by the State Governments or State training institutes for capacity-building of stakeholders,`
  line `Government including its functionaries, civil society members, corporate sector and people's elected`
  line representatives;
  line
  line `(f) develop educational materials for disaster management including academic and professional`
  line courses;
  line
  line `(g) promote awareness among stakeholders including college or school teachers and students,`
  line `technical personnel and others associated with multi-hazard mitigation, preparedness and response`
  line measures;
  line
  line `(h) undertake, Organise and facilitate study courses, conferences, lectures, seminars within and`
  line `outside the country to promote the aforesaid objects;`
  line
  line `(i) undertake and provide for publication of journals, research papers and books and establish and`
  line `maintain libraries in furtherance of the aforesaid objects;`
  line
  line `(j) do all such other lawful things as are conducive or incidental to the attainment of the above`
  line `objects; and`
  line
  line `(k) undertake any other function as may be assigned to it by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (8174)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 46
  title `Officers, employees, experts and consultants of the National Institute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2025, s. 24, for section 43 (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8174&sectionno=43&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `^1[43. Officers, employees, experts and consultants of National Institute.--- (1) The Central`
  line `Government shall provide the National Institute of Disaster Management with such officers, other`
  line `employees and consultants, as it considers necessary, for carrying out its functions.`
  line
  line `(2) The National Institute may recruit experts as per norms approved by the Central Government to`
  line `perform such functions as provided in sub-section (9) of section 42.`
  line
  line `(3) The salaries, allowances payable to officers and employees and the other terms and conditions of`
  line `their service shall be such as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (8175)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 47
  title `National Disaster Response Force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2025, s. 25, for "NATIONAL DISASTER RESPONSE FORCE" (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8175&sectionno=44&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `CHAPTER VIII`
  line
  line `^1[DISASTER RESPONSE FORCE]`
  line
  line `(1) There shall be constituted a National Disaster`
  line `Response Force for the purpose of specialist response to a threatening disaster situation or disaster.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Force shall be constituted in such manner and, the`
  line `conditions of service of the members of the Force, including disciplinary provisions therefore, be such as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_a:
  sectionId (96440)
  sectionNo 44A
  orderNo 48
  title `State Disaster Response Force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2025, s. 26, (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=96440&sectionno=44A&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_44_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[44A. State Disaster Response Force.---(1) The State Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, constitute a State Disaster Response Force for the purpose of specialist response to a`
  line `threatening disaster situation or disaster.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the State Disaster Response Force shall be constituted in`
  line `such manner, with such functions and the terms and conditions of service of the members of such Force`
  line `shall be such as may be prescribed by the State Government concerned.]`
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (8176)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 49
  title `Control, direction, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8176&sectionno=45&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `The general superintendence, direction and control of the Force shall`
  line `be vested and exercised by the National Authority and the command and supervision of the Force shall`
  line `vest in an officer to be appointed by the Central Government as the Director General of the National`
  line `Disaster Response Force.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (8177)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 50
  title `National Disaster Response Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8177&sectionno=46&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, constitute a fund to be called the National Disaster Response Fund ^1[for meeting`
  line `different aspects of disaster management] and there shall be credited thereto---`
  line
  line `(a) an amount which the Central Government may, after due appropriation made by Parliament`
  line `by law in this behalf provide;`
  line
  line `(b) any grants that may be made by any person or institution for the purpose of disaster`
  line management.
  line
  line `^2[(2) The Fund constituted under sub-section (1), shall be applied in accordance with the guidelines`
  line `laid down by the Central Government in consultation with the National Authority.]`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2025, s. 27, for "for meeting any threatening disaster situation or disaster" (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by , s. 27, ibid., for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (8178)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 51
  title `National Disaster Mitigation Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8178&sectionno=47&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, constitute a Fund to be called the National Disaster Mitigation Fund ^1[for meeting`
  line `disaster mitigation needs] and there shall be credited thereto such amount which the Central Government`
  line `may, after due appropriation made by Parliament by law in this behalf, provide.`
  line
  line `^2[(2) The Fund constituted under sub-section (1), shall be applied in accordance with the guidelines`
  line `laid down by the Central Government in consultation with the National Authority.]`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2025, s. 28, for "for projects exclusively for the purpose of mitigation" (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 28, ibid., for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (8179)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 52
  title `Establishment of funds by State Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by y Act 10 of 2025, s. 29, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8179&sectionno=48&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government shall, immediately`
  line `after notifications issued for constituting the State Authority and the District Authorities, establish for the`
  line `purposes of this Act the following funds, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the fund to be called the State Disaster Response Fund;`
  line
  line `(b) the fund to be called the District Disaster Response Fund;`
  line
  line `(c) the fund to be called the State Disaster Mitigation Fund;`
  line
  line `(d) the fund to be called the District Disaster Mitigation Fund.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) The State Government shall ensure that the funds established---`
  line
  line `(i) under clauses (a) and (c) of sub-section (1) are available to the State Executive Committee and`
  line `the State Authority respectively and are applied as per the guidelines issued by the Central`
  line `Government in consultation with the National Authority;`
  line
  line `(ii) under clauses(b) and (d) of sub-section (1) are available to the District Authority.]`
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (8180)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 53
  title `Allocation of funds by Ministries and Departments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8180&sectionno=49&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Ministry or Department of the`
  line `Government of India shall make provisions, in its annual budget, for funds for the purposes of carrying`
  line `out the activities and programmes set out in its disaster management plan.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall, mutatis mutandis, apply to departments of the Government`
  line `of the State.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (8181)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 54
  title `Emergency procurement and accounting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2025, s. 30, (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8181&sectionno=50&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `Where by reason of any threatening disaster`
  line `situation or disaster, the National Authority or the State Authority or the District Authority ^1[or the Urban`
  line `Authority] is satisfied that`
  line `immediate procurement of provisions or materials or the immediate application of resources are necessary`
  line `for rescue or relief,---`
  line
  line `(a) it may authorise the concerned department or authority to make the emergency procurement`
  line `and in such case, the standard procedure requiring inviting of tenders shall be deemed to be waived;`
  line
  line `(b) a certificate about utilisation of provisions or materials by the controlling officer authorised by`
  line `the National Authority, State Authority or District Authority ^1[or Urban Authority], as the case may be, shall be deemed to`
  line `be a valid document or voucher for the purpose of accounting of emergency, procurement of such`
  line `provisions or materials`
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (8182)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 55
  title `Punishment for obstruction, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2025, s. 31 (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8182&sectionno=51&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, without reasonable cause---`
  line
  line `(a) obstructs any officer or employee of the Central Government or the State Government, or a`
  line `person authorised by the National Authority or State Authority or District Authority ^1[or Urban`
  line `Authority] in the discharge`
  line `of his functions under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) refuses to comply with any direction given by or on behalf of the Central Government or the`
  line `State Government or the National Executive Committee or the State Executive Committee or the`
  line `District Authority ^1[or Urban`
  line `Authority] under this Act,`
  line
  line `shall on conviction be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year or with`
  line `fine, or with both, and if such obstruction or refusal to comply with directions results in loss of lives or`
  line `imminent danger thereof, shall on conviction be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to two years.`
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (8183)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 56
  title `Punishment for false claim.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2025, s. 32, for "or the District Authority" (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8183&sectionno=52&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `Whoever knowingly makes a claim which he knows or has reason`
  line `to believe to be false for obtaining any relief, assistance, repair, reconstruction or other benefits`
  line `consequent to disaster from any officer of the Central Government, the State Government, the National`
  line `Authority, the State Authority ^1[, the District Authority or the Urban Authority], shall, on conviction be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years, and also with fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (8184)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 57
  title `Punishment for misappropriation of money or materials, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8184&sectionno=53&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, being entrusted with`
  line `any money or materials, or otherwise being, in custody of, or dominion over, any money or goods, meant`
  line `for providing relief in any threatening disaster situation or disaster, misappropriates or appropriates for his`
  line `own use or disposes of such money or materials or any part thereof or wilfully compels any other person`
  line `so to do, shall on conviction be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years,`
  line `and also with fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (8185)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 58
  title `Punishment for false warning.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8185&sectionno=54&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `Whoever makes or circulates a false alarm or warning as to`
  line `disaster or its severity or magnitude, leading to panic, shall on conviction, be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment which may extend to one year or with fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (8186)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 59
  title `Offences by Departments of the Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8186&sectionno=55&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by any Department of the Government, the head of the Department shall be deemed to be`
  line `guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly unless he`
  line `proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he exercised all due diligence to`
  line `prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a Department of the Government and it is proved that the offence has been committed with`
  line `the consent or connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any officer, other than the`
  line `head of the Department, such officer shall be deemed to be guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be`
  line `proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (8187)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 60
  title `Failure of officer in duty or his connivance at the contravention of the provisions of this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes `1. Numbered and ins. by Act 10 of 2025, s. 33, (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8187&sectionno=56&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `^1[1] Any officer, on whom any duty has been imposed by or under this Act and who ceases or`
  line `refuses to perform or withdraws himself from the duties of his office shall, unless he has obtained the`
  line `express written permission of his official superior or has other lawful excuse for so doing, be punishable`
  line `with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year or with fine.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) Notwithstanding any action under sub-section (1), it shall be lawful for the State Government on`
  line `its own or on the directions given by the Central Government to take such disciplinary action under the`
  line `relevant rules, against any officer who ceases or refuses to perform or withdraws himself from the duties`
  line `of his office or on grounds of insubordination or dereliction of duty during a disaster:`
  line
  line `Provided that the action taken by the State Government shall not be inconsistent with the directions`
  line `given by the Central Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (8188)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 61
  title `Penalty for contravention of any order regarding requisitioning.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8188&sectionno=57&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `If any person contravenes`
  line `any order made under section 65, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend`
  line `to one year or with fine or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (8189)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 62
  title `Offence by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8189&sectionno=58&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a company`
  line `or body corporate, every person who at the time the offence was committed, was in charge of, and was`
  line `responsible to, the company, for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed to be guilty of the contravention and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished`
  line `accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any punishment`
  line `provided in this Act, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he`
  line `exercised due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company, and it is proved that the offence was committed with the consent or connivance`
  line `of or is attributable to any neglect on the part of any director, manager, secretary or other officer of the`
  line `company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also, be deemed to be guilty of that`
  line `offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purpose of this section—`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (8190)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 63
  title `Previous sanction for prosecution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2025, s. 34, for "and 56" (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8190&sectionno=59&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `No prosecution for offences punishable under sections 55`
  line `^1[and sub-section (1) of section 56] shall be instituted except with the previous sanction of the Central Government or the State`
  line `Government, as the case may be, or of any officer authorised in this behalf, by general or special order, by`
  line `such Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (8191)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 64
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2025, s. 35, (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8191&sectionno=60&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `No court shall take cognizance of an offence under this Act except on`
  line `a complaint made by---`
  line
  line `(a) the National Authority, the State Authority, the Central Government, the State Government,`
  line `the District Authority ^1[, the Urban Authority] or any other authority or officer authorised in this behalf by that Authority or`
  line `Government, as the case may be; or`
  line
  line `(b) any person who has given notice of not less than thirty days in the manner prescribed, of the`
  line `alleged offence and his intention to make a complaint to the National Authority, the State Authority,`
  line `the Central Government, the State Government, the District Authority ^1[, the Urban Authority] or any other authority or`
  line `officer authorised as aforesaid.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_a:
  sectionId (96443)
  sectionNo 60A
  orderNo 65
  title `Power of Central Government or State Government to take action in relation to nature of hazard and punishment for its contravention.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2025, s. 36, (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=96443&sectionno=60A&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_60_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[60A. Power of Central Government or State Government to take action in relation to nature`
  line `of hazard and punishment for its contravention.--- (1) The Central Government or the State`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, require any person to take any action or refrain`
  line `from taking any action, in relation to the nature of the hazard, which in the opinion of the Central`
  line `Government or the State Government, as the case may be, is required for reducing the impact of a`
  line disaster.
  line
  line `(2) Any notification issued under this section shall be valid for a period specified therein or six`
  line `months, whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `(3) Whoever contravenes the provisions of this section shall be liable to pay a penalty as specified in`
  line `the notification of the Central Government or the State Government, as the case may be:`
  line `Provided that the penalty referred to in this sub-section shall not exceed ten thousand rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (8192)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 66
  title `Prohibition against discrimination.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes `1. The words "compensation and" omitted by Act 10 of 2025, s. 37 (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8192&sectionno=61&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `While providing ^1*** relief to the victims of disaster,`
  line `there shall be no discrimination on the ground of sex, caste, community, descent or religion.`
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (8193)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 67
  title `Power to issue direction by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8193&sectionno=62&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any`
  line `other law for the time being in force, it shall be lawful for the Central Government to issue direction in`
  line `writing to the Ministries or Departments of the Government of India, or the National Executive`
  line `Committee or the State Government, State Authority, State Executive Committee, statutory bodies or any`
  line `of its officers or employees, as the case may be, to facilitate or assist in the disaster management and such`
  line `Ministry or Department or Government or Authority, Executive Committee, statutory body, officer or`
  line `employee shall be bound to comply with such direction.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (8194)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 68
  title `Powers to be made available for rescue operations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2025, s. 38, (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8194&sectionno=63&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `Any officer or authority of the Union or a`
  line `State, when requested by the National Executive Committee, any State Executive Committee or District`
  line `Authority ^1[or Urban Authority] or any person authorised by such Committee or Authority in this behalf, shall make available to`
  line `that Committee or authority or person, such officers and employees as requested for, to perform any of`
  line `the functions in connection with the prevention of disaster or mitigation or rescue or relief work.`
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (8195)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 69
  title `Making or amending rules, etc., in certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes `!. Ins. by Act 10 of 2025, s. 39, (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8195&sectionno=64&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, if it appears to the National Executive Committee, State Executive Committee or the District`
  line `Authority ^1[or the Urban Authority], as the case may be, that provisions of any rule, regulation, notification, guideline, instruction,`
  line `order, scheme or bye-laws, as the case may be, are required to be made or amended for the purposes of`
  line `prevention of disasters or the mitigation thereof, it may require the amendment of such rules, regulation, notification, guidelines, instruction, order, scheme or bye-laws, as the case may be, for that purpose, and`
  line `the appropriate department or authority shall take necessary action to comply with the requirements.`
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (8196)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 70
  title `Power of requisition of resources, provisions, vehicles, etc., for rescue operations, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8196&sectionno=65&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `(1) If`
  line `it appears to the National Executive Committee, State Executive Committee or District Authority`
  line `^1[or Urban Authority] or any officer as may be authorised by it in this behalf that---`
  line
  line `(a) any resources with any authority or person are needed for the purpose of prompt response;`
  line
  line `(b) any premises are needed or likely to be needed for the purpose of rescue operations; or`
  line
  line `(c) any vehicle is needed or is likely to be needed for the purposes of transport of' resources from`
  line `disaster affected areas or transport of resources to the affected area or transport in connection with`
  line `rescue, rehabilitation or reconstruction,`
  line
  line `such authority may, by order in writing, requisition such resources or premises or such vehicle, as the case`
  line `may be, and may make such further orders as may appear to it to be necessary or expedient in connection`
  line `with the requisitioning.`
  line
  line `(2) Whenever any resource, premises or vehicle is requisitioned under sub-section (1), the period of`
  line `such requisition shall not extend beyond the period for which such resource, premises or vehicle is`
  line `required for any of the purposes mentioned in that sub-section.`
  line
  line `(3) In this section,---`
  line
  line `^2[(a) "resources" includes human and material resources, and equipment;]`
  line
  line `(b) "services" includes facilities;`
  line
  line `(c) "premises" means any land, building or part of a building and includes a hut, shed or other`
  line `structure or any part thereof;`
  line
  line `(d) "vehicle" means any vehicle used or capable of being used for the purpose of transport,`
  line `whether propelled by mechanical power or otherwise.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2025, s. 40, (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 40, ibid., for clause (a) (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (8197)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 71
  title `Payment of compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8197&sectionno=66&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever any Committee, Authority or officer referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 65, in pursuance of that section requisitions any premises, there shall be paid to`
  line `the persons interested compensation the amount of which shall be determined by taking into consideration`
  line `the following, namely:—`
  line
  line `(i) the rent payable in respect of the premises, or if no rent is so payable, the rent payable for`
  line `similar premises in the locality;`
  line
  line `(ii) if as consequence of the requisition of the premises the person interested is compelled to`
  line `change his residence or place of business, the reasonable expenses (if any) incidental to such change:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any person interested being aggrieved by the amount of compensation so`
  line `determined makes an application within the thirty days to the Central Government or the State`
  line `Government, as the case may be, for referring the matter to an arbitrator, the amount of compensation to`
  line `be paid shall be such as the arbitrator appointed in this behalf by the Central Government or the State`
  line `Government, as the case may be, may determine:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where there is any dispute as to the title to receive the compensation or as to the`
  line `apportionment of the amount of compensation, it shall be referred by the Central Government or the State`
  line `Government, as the case may be, to an arbitrator appointed in this behalf by the Central Government or`
  line `the State Government, as the case may be, for determination, and shall be determined in accordance with`
  line `the decision of such arbitrator.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—In this sub-section, the expression "person interested" means the person who was in`
  line `actual possession of the premises requisitioned under section 65 immediately before the requisition, or`
  line `where no person was in such actual possession, the owner of such premises.`
  line
  line `(2) Whenever any Committee, Authority or officer, referred to in sub-section (1) of section 65 in`
  line `pursuance of that section requisitions any vehicle, there shall be paid to the owner thereof compensation`
  line `the mount of which shall be determined by the Central Government or the State Government, as the case`
  line `may be, on the basis of the fares or rates prevailing in the locality for the hire of such vehicle:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the owner of such vehicle being aggrieved by the amount of compensation so`
  line `determined makes an application within the prescribed time to the Central Government or the State`
  line `Government, as the case may be, for referring the matter to an arbitrator, the amount of compensation to`
  line `be paid shall be such as the arbitrator appointed in this behalf by the Central Government or the State`
  line `Government, as the case may be, may determine:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where immediately before the requisitioning the vehicle or vessel was by virtue`
  line `of a hire purchase agreement in the possession of a person other than the owner, the amount determined`
  line `under this sub-section as the total compensation payable in respect of the requisition shall be apportioned`
  line `between that person and the owner in such manner as they may agree upon, and in default of agreement,`
  line `in such manner as an arbitrator appointed by the Central Government or the State Government, as the case`
  line `may be, in this behalf may decide.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (8198)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 72
  title `Direction to media for communication of warnings, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2025, s. 41, for "or a District Authority" (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8198&sectionno=67&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `The National Authority, the State`
  line `Authority ^1[, a District Authority or an Urban Authority] may recommend to the Government to give direction to any authority or`
  line `person in control of any audio or audio-visual media or such other means of communication as may be`
  line `available to carry any warning or advisories regarding any threatening disaster situation or disaster, and`
  line `the said means of communication and media as designated shall comply with such direction.`
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (8199)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 73
  title `Authentication of orders of decisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2025, s. 42, for "or the District Authority" (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8199&sectionno=68&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `Every order or decision of the National Authority or`
  line `the National Executive Committee, the State Authority, or the State Executive Committee ^1[, a District`
  line `Authority or an Urban Authority], shall be authenticated by such officers of the National Authority or the`
  line `National Executive Committee or, the State Executive Committee ^1[, a District Authority or an Urban`
  line `Authority], as may be authorised by it in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (8200)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 74
  title `Delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2025, s. 43, (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8200&sectionno=69&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `The National Executive Committee, State Executive Committee`
  line `^1[National Authority, State Authority, District Authority or Urban Authority], as the case may be, by`
  line `general or special order in writing, may delegate to the Chairperson or any other member or to any`
  line `officer, subject to such conditions and limitations, if any, as may be specified in the order, such of its`
  line `powers and functions under this Act as it may deem necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (8201)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 75
  title `Annual report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8201&sectionno=70&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `(1) The National Authority shall prepare once every year, in such form and at`
  line `such time as may be prescribed, an annual report giving a true and full account of its activities during the`
  line `previous year and copies thereof shall be forwarded to the Central Government and that Government shall`
  line `cause the same to be laid before both Houses of Parliament within one month of its receipt.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Authority shall prepare once in every year, in such form and at such time as may be`
  line `prescribed, an annual report giving a true and full account of its activities during the previous year and`
  line `copies thereof shall be forwarded to the State Government and that Government shall cause the same to`
  line `be laid before each House of the State Legislature where it consists of two Houses, or where such`
  line `Legislature consists of one House, before that House.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (8202)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 76
  title `Bar of jurisdiction of court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2025, s. 44, for "or District Authority" (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8202&sectionno=71&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `No court (except the Supreme Court or a High Court) shall have`
  line `jurisdiction to entertain any suit or proceeding in respect of anything done, action taken, orders made,`
  line `direction, instruction or guidelines issued by the Central Government, National Authority, State`
  line `Government, State Authority ^1[, District Authority or Urban Authority] in pursuance of any power conferred by, or in relation`
  line `to its functions, by this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (8203)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 77
  title `Act to have overriding effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8203&sectionno=72&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act, shall have effect, notwithstanding`
  line `anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the time being in force or in any instrument`
  line `having effect by virtue of any law other than this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (8204)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 78
  title `Action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2025, s. 45, (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8204&sectionno=73&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `No suit or prosecution or other proceeding shall lie in any court`
  line `against the Central Government or the National Authority or the State Government or the State Authority`
  line `or the District Authority ^1[or the Urban Authority] or local authority or any officer or employee of the Central Government or the`
  line `National Authority or the State Government or the State Authority or the District Authority ^1[or the Urban Authority] or local`
  line `authority or any person working for on behalf of such Government or authority in respect of any work`
  line `done or purported to have been done or intended to be done in good faith by such authority or`
  line `Government or such officer or employee or such person under the provisions of this Act or the rules or`
  line `regulations made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (8205)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 79
  title `Immunity from legal process.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2025, s. 46, for "or District Authority" (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8205&sectionno=74&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `Officers and employees of the Central Government, National`
  line `Authority, National Executive Committee, State Government, State Authority, State Executive`
  line `Committee ^1[, District Authority or Urban Authority] shall be immune from legal process in regard to any warning in respect`
  line `of any impending disaster communicated or disseminated by them in their official capacity or any action`
  line `taken or direction issued by them in pursuance of such communication or dissemination.`
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (8206)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 80
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2025, s. 47 (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8206&sectionno=75&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the composition and number of the members of the National Authority under sub-section (2),`
  line `and the term of office and conditions of service of members of the National Authority under`
  line `sub-section (4), of section 3;`
  line
  line `^1[(aa) the salaries, allowances and other terms and conditions of service of officers, other`
  line `employees, experts and consultants of the National Authority under sub-section (3) of section 5;]`
  line
  line `(b) the allowances to be paid to the members of the advisory committee under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 7;`
  line
  line `(c) the powers and functions of the Chairperson of the National Executive Committee under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 8 and the procedure to be followed by the National Executive Committee in`
  line `exercise of its powers and discharge of its functions under sub-section (4) of section 8;`
  line
  line `^1[(ca) the procedure to be followed by the National Crisis Management Committee in exercise of`
  line `its powers and discharging of its functions under sub-section (4) of section 8A;]`
  line
  line `(d) allowances to be paid to the persons associated with the sub-committee constituted by the`
  line `National Executive Committee under sub-section (3) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(e) the number of members of the National Institute of Disaster Management under sub-section`
  line `(2), the term of the office and vacancies among members and the manner of filling such vacancies`
  line `under sub-section (3) and the manner of constituting the Governing Body of the National Institute of`
  line `Disaster Management under sub-section (4) of section 42;`
  line
  line `^1[(ea) the salaries, allowances and the other terms and conditions of service of officers and other`
  line `employees of the National Institute under sub-section (3) of section 43;]`
  line
  line `(f) the manner of constitution of the Force, the conditions of service of the members of the Force,`
  line `including disciplinary provisions under sub-section (2) of section 44;`
  line
  line `(g) the manner in which notice of the offence and of the intention to make a complaint to the`
  line `National Authority, the State Authority, the Central Government, the State Government or the other`
  line `authority or officer under clause (b) of section 60;`
  line
  line `(h) the form in which and the time within which annual report is to be prepared under section 70;`
  line
  line `(i) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed, or in respect of which provision is to be`
  line `made by rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (8207)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 81
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8207&sectionno=76&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `(1) The National Institute of Disaster Management, with the`
  line `previous approval of the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make`
  line `regulations consistent with this Act and the rules made thereunder to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) powers and functions to be exercised and discharged by the governing body;`
  line
  line `(b) procedure to be followed by the governing body in exercise of the powers and discharge of its`
  line functions;
  line
  line `(c) any other matter for which under this Act provision may be made by the regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76_a:
  sectionId (96445)
  sectionNo 76A
  orderNo 82
  title `Power of National Authority to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2025, s. 48, (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=96445&sectionno=76A&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_76_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[76A. Power of National Authority to make regulations.--- Without prejudice to the provisions of`
  line `section 76, the National Authority, with the previous approval of the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, make regulations, other than regulations made under section 76,`
  line `consistent with the provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder to carry out the purposes of this`
  line Act.]
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (8208)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 83
  title `Rules and regulations to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2025, s. 49 (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8208&sectionno=77&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `Every rule made by the Central`
  line `Government and every regulation made by the National Institute of Disaster Management ^1[and the`
  line `National Authority] under this Act`
  line `shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session,`
  line `for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised of one session or in two or more successive`
  line `sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive`
  line `sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or regulation or both Houses`
  line `agree that the rule or regulation should not be made, the rule or regulation shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule or`
  line regulation.
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (8209)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 84
  title `Power of State Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2025, s. 50 (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8209&sectionno=78&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, make rules to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the composition and number of the members of the State Authority under sub-section (2), and`
  line `the term of office and conditions of service of the members of the State Authority under sub-section`
  line `(5), of section 14;`
  line
  line `(b) the allowances to be paid to the members of the advisory committee under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 17;`
  line
  line `(c) the powers and functions of the Chairperson of the State Executive Committee under`
  line `sub-section (3), and the procedure to be followed by the State Executive Committee in exercise of its`
  line `powers and discharge of its functions under sub-section (4) of section 20;`
  line
  line `(d) allowances to be paid to the persons associated with the sub-committee constituted by the`
  line `State Executive Committee under sub-section (3) of section 21;`
  line
  line `(e) the composition and the number of members of the District Authority under sub-section (2),`
  line `and the powers and functions to be exercised and discharged by the Chief Executive Officer of the`
  line `District Authority under sub-section (3) of section 25;`
  line
  line `(f) allowances payable to the persons associated with any committee constituted by the District`
  line `Authority as experts under sub-section (3) of section 28;`
  line
  line `^1[(fa) the powers, functions and other matters relating to Urban Authority under sub-section (6) of`
  line `section 41A;`
  line
  line `(fb) the manner of constitution of State Disaster Response Force, its functions and the terms and`
  line `conditions of service of members of such Force under sub-section (2) of section 44A;]`
  line
  line `(g) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed, or in respect of which provision is to`
  line `be made by rules.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the State Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is`
  line `made, before each House of the State Legislature where it consists of two Houses, or where such`
  line `Legislature consists of one House before that House.`
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (8210)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 85
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2025, s. 51 (w.e.f. 9-4-2025).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022&sectionId=8210&sectionno=79&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00053_200553_1517807327022
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government or the State Government, as the case may be, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, make order not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as may appear to it to be`
  line `necessary or expedient for the removal of the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiration of two years from the commencement`
  line `of this Act.`
  line
  line `^1[(1A) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), if any difficulty arises in giving effect`
  line `to the provisions of this Act as amended by the Disaster Management (Amendment) Act, 2025, the`
  line `Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions not`
  line `inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as may appear to it to be necessary or expedient for removing`
  line `the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made under this sub-section after the expiry of a period of three`
  line `years from the date of commencement of the Disaster Management (Amendment) Act, 2025.]`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament or the Legislature, as the case may be.`
